  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nWe should implement the standard [Remote Key Manager](https://ethereum.github.io/keymanager-APIs/#/Remote%20Key%20Manager) API in Lighthouse.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\n* We can hook into the authenticated routing for the existing VC APIs [here](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/c475499dfe9c2df52b2810054ed2c3b59d4988f8/validator_client/src/http_api/mod.rs#L537).\r\n* The POST method should be quite similar to [`create_validators_web3signer`](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/c475499dfe9c2df52b2810054ed2c3b59d4988f8/validator_client/src/http_api/create_validator.rs#L166).\r\n* The DELETE method will be more involved, but similar to the non-web3-signer [`delete`](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/c475499dfe9c2df52b2810054ed2c3b59d4988f8/validator_client/src/http_api/keystores.rs#L211). It would be good to re-use [`delete_definition_and_keystore`](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/c475499dfe9c2df52b2810054ed2c3b59d4988f8/validator_client/src/initialized_validators.rs#L443) between the two implementations. It will need slight modifications to remove the error [here](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/c475499dfe9c2df52b2810054ed2c3b59d4988f8/validator_client/src/initialized_validators.rs#L463).\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nv2.1.3",
